{"id": "1443349984631329053", "channel_id": "1443349984631329053", "type": 0, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "It seems that some forms of bonus to damage, like Corposant Soulforge, is on the same layer of Fortress on enemies, so an enemy that had 99% reduction because of 99 Fortress, will still take almost full or completely full damage at max level, like in this video b64776be-47b4-3305-8026-6686e2dfad2b#E#a.\nIs this intended behavior? \nWanted to share because i don't want that other instances like these, that can fundamentally break a fight, could happen in the future.\nSo that the fight itself can be toned down if too problematic for everyone without having to rely on strange and limited interactions, if that is indeed a bug.", "timestamp": "2025-11-26T21:17:32.482000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-26T21:27:08.324000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 3}], "attachments": [{"id": "1443349985130319902", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 182220, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1443349984631329053/1443349985130319902/image.png?ex=6a004d2c&is=69fefbac&hm=736d91fa543172ab617f036e6a42c34f1894a2277125fbc77723488f738d4ded&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1443349984631329053", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Bonus Damage and Fortress", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1181168103141416960", "1361168893200044183"]}
